caption: Have always wanted to try a mochi donut! We came all the way from Rhode Island to visit Oahu / try all the food and MoDo was on my list. these donuts did not disappoint. Even my picky toddlers ate three!!
fresh donuts 11am sharp I'm here
Stay away from this place if you're trying to diet.
Delicious mochi donuts! They were really good.
Wow!! Best mochi donuts on the island. The lilikoi is my favorite.

This location is very hard to find. Especially on a Monday during COVID (a lot of things closed, hard to ask for help with no many people around.)  It’s in the Japanese Market on the second floor (the name of the market is on the signs throughout but not the donut shop name), there is a food hall on the first floor that is closed on Monday... making things very confusing. There were only six flavors at this location, which surprised me. The cookies and cream, strawberry, and passion fruit were our favorites. They have a great texture and are something unique to try. The Japanese flavors weren’t my favorite, (not sweet enough) but I am American 😉

(Translated by Google) It's chewy and delicious ㅎㅎ I ate chocolate, black sesame, and matcha but it wasn't too sweet and the matcha was the most delicious~  (Original) 쫄깃하고 맛있어요 ㅎㅎ 초콜렛, 검은깨, 맛차 세가지 먹었는데 많이 달지 않았고 맛차가 제일 맛있었어요~
WE LOVE MODO HAWAII!!! Lilikoi is my favourite!!!
Really good mochi donuts! I really liked the matcha and cookies&cream ones that I got. We also tried the lilikoi one, but fair warning it is super sweet!

To get here: go inside international market onto the second floor inside the Japanese market. You’ll find it when you go wayyyyy to the back. Took me way too long for average mochi donuts :/ I don’t suggest coming late in the evening because they may serve old donuts from the day!

If I could eat a mochi donut every day I probably would. Like regular donuts but lighter and chewier and OMG I can't stop thinking about them. We liked the churro and chocolate best.  We had difficulties finding Modo originally! It's just inside the mall, go upstairs to Mitsuwa Marketplace and it's in the back 🙂
Located inside a Japanese gift/grocery store. Nice variety of mochi donuts. Reminds me of Pon de Ring from Mr. Donuts
Mochi donuts! Buy a dozen and get 1 free. The shop counter is inside international mall’s mitsuwa
Mochi donuts are very tasty and delicious!
Hidden in the back of the market. The donuts are good. Wish they could re-warm them a bit.
5% off when you check-in on Yelp. Check-in every few hours!
Has a chewy texture that makes it unique. There were a variety of flavors to choose from. Lilikoi was definitely my favorite. Quite pricey.
So delicious I ate all 3 in one sitting!

When the store first opened their Donuts were fresh and good. Now they are not busy.  Their  donuts are cold, not fresh. It’s taste like old donuts from the day before. My son ate it and it made his stomach felt uncomfortable. That would be my last time going there.

OMG what a discovery. As a donut lover it’s exciting to find new manifestations of them! The lilikoi and the purple yam are both particular delicious—soft and chewy with real icing. Super kind service too 😊😊
They have friendly service but honestly the mochi is so bland and doesnt have much flavor. I would not recommend this place nor will I come back.
Unique

I was excited to try it for our visit to Oahu.  Tried ones in mister donut in Japan and excited similar qualities.  It was disappointing as the donut itself was not crispy outside. The topping was okay, but donut was soft and not chewy like the mochi texture.  It was overpriced for charging over $2 for this quality.

Tucked away in the back MoDo is a nice friendly little shop. The mochi donuts are great. Nice texture, a bit heavy but the flavors I tried were not overly sweet. There are some great flavors to choose from. You definitely cannot eat a whole bunch of these alone or all at once as the weight and sweetness does add up. Best to share with a group so you can try the different flavors. My favorite was the black sesame.
It can take a minute to get the staff’s attention, but the mochi donuts are great, good luck finding anything in Waikiki for breakfast any cheaper.

Visiting Hawaii from San Jose, CA and was super stoked to get some fresh MoDo since I usually only get it every so often when they do a pop-up in my area. Unfortunately they were sold out of 2 flavors I wanted (which is understandable since I got there an hour before they closed), but I was even more bummed that I had ordered 6 expecting them to be delicious like they are at the pop-ups and I was given cold, soft MoDo. The frosting still tasted really good but they DEFINITELY weren't fresh. Tasted more like day old MoDo = Maybe you have to get there when they open to get fresh ones but I'd suggest just skipping if you can't get there early on.

Surprisingly delicious.  Thought it was just another doughnut with mochi inside and frosting on top.  Actually mochi is mixed in with dough making it kind of chewy.  Frosting wasn't overwhelmingly sweet.  Very nice surprise, kept wanting more.

To anyone going tomorrow and Monday. Note: please try to arrive before 10am, otherwise you will end up waiting 3 hours. This is because there is no limit on the amount of boxes you can get. multiple people ordering 6-8 boxes means a longer wait. Had I'd known, I would have thought twice before going and I agree with a previous yelper that there should have been a limit to prevent running out of ingredients, and having a shorter wait. Note there are 3 people running the pop up as well.  But despite the long wait, the donuts were fluffy, fresh, bubbly, and for some reason it reminded me of a funnel cake. I got a dozen which included the taro sugar, blueberry and black sesame. I surprisingly loved the black sesame. It reminded me of a classic red bean mochi, it wasn't too sweet and really good. The blueberry didnt taste artificial at all and tasted like fresh blueberries. The one I didnt enjoy so much was the taro sugar only because it was mostly like sugar.  An update is that I just got to try them again. The donuts deflated and now I get why it its called modo. The donuts now have the exact consistency of mochi. Like before it was mostly more of a donut but now its flavored mochi. I wish I can get more, but the line though...
The donuts are delicious and great for satisfying sweet cravings. The price is fair and they're always freshly made which gives it that perfect taste.

One of the surprise highlights of our Honolulu visit has to be these Mochi Donuts from @modohawaii. The store is a bit hidden away in the Mitsuwa Marketplace, which itself is inside of the International Marketplace in Waikiki. Normally we aren’t big fans of donuts, but these are amazing! The mochi adds a new dimension of chewiness to each bite and they truly combine the best qualities of both a traditional Japanese mochi and a fried donut. This is definitely going to be a spot we will visit again on our next visit to Hawaii!
hard to find (inside mitsuwa) Cookies and cream was great
Love it! Love the texture of mochi & donut combination.. not too sweet. Has many flavors for everyones liking... People working behind the counter are nice and friendly!

Their Black Sesame Mochi doughnut is delicious! I also tried their Early Grey, and as a tea lover, it was a special treat and find. The coffee served is illy coffee, and while I'm not a coffee drinker, my mum really likes their coffee. She states it is high quality and for 1.99 a cup, it's worth a try! Definitely highly recommend and will return!
Donuts were great and service was great.  My only regret is ringing the bell knowing that the cashier was doing something less than 5 feet away.

The donuts are always tasty, but when I get one of each flavors I would like the attendant to be at least semi-kind. The lady with glasses assumed I knew their promotions and made us feel unwelcomed. Will be back for the donuts, not for the customer service unfortunately..

Very tasty donuts: subtle flavours and not too sweet.  Black sesame, matcha green tea and cookies&cream varieties were favourites.  The coffee was good.  The seating area which is shared with several food outlets is a good place.

Expected them to be fresh but they were pre made, maybe because I was there at 9pm. This place is also hard to find because it's on level 1 and inside the Japanese supermarket as you come up the escalators. Matcha love was better which is opposite this store

Very interesting donuts! It was my first time trying mochi donuts, they are slightly chewy and interesting shaped! The passion fruit donut was my favourite, it had a good strong passion fruit flavour.
Great taste of matcha donut
Was good expected more from what I have been told
Very friendly staff! 💞

Pretty good! Some flavors better than others, of course. I'd recommend the honey glaze, the illy espresso, the early grey, and the matcha for sure! Would love to come back but sadly I'm from California haha.

There are mochi donuts and then there are MoDo donuts! Tucked in the back of Mitsuwa on the second floor of International Market Place, MoDo offers a great variety of flavors - try the black sesame, for sure!

Located in the International Market, 2nd floor, inside the Mitsuwa Market.  Fantastic service! They were so kind.  I was so curious to try these cute donuts... it was a bit of a disappointment.  I ordered the black sesame, matcha, honey glaze, cookies & cream, and the earl grey.  The matcha flavor was weak. Surprisingly, the favorite was the cookies and cream. I had high hopes for matcha and black sesame. Black sesame wasn’t bad but not great.  The donuts had a very slight taste of oil. The aftertaste was unpleasant.  Overall, the donuts were a mediocre experience.
DONUTS ARE AWESOME! fairly cheap, and service is great! then when you're done eating you can check out the market place!
Somehow this didn't taste as good as the pop-up in SF. They came out very cold and not that tasty.
Nicely displayed and labeled.
Yummy donuts! The cookies and cream one was probably my favorite. I think they're definitely worth trying.
These donuts are so good! They aren't like the typical donuts you may be used to where it's cake like.. these are more spongy but really good. !
Love the mochi donut and service is always quick.
I absolutely loved it.. I can say that this is my favorite donut... I am hooked😃.. I am craving for real...
The 4 star reviewers are haters. This place is amazing
Chewy and light! Loved the Key Lime!
Great donuts!

Good spot for mochi donuts. Inside the Mitsuwa marketplace store on the second floor of the international marketplace🤔. We tried the honey glazed, coconut, black sesame, cookies & cream and espresso. We like most of them but the espresso. The espresso was a bit overcooked or something. It just wasnt as soft as the others. Will go again. If you are nearby try it out.
First time at MoDo and those mochi donuts are addicting!  Delicious!
Yummy chewy mochi donuts! They have seasonal flavors and kamaaina discount

These mochi donuts are a little different. Ended up getting the black sesame, strawberry, and Passionfruit flavours. Not sure if the ones we had were fresh or not, but the best description would be like a moist donut the next day. The flavours were nice, not over powering, not weak in flavour like other trendy donuts I’ve had in the past.

Light, chewy and offered in a variety of awesome flavors, mochi doughnuts are the best category of doughnuts (sorry Leonard). Since my first visit to Mister Donut in Taiwan ten years ago, I have been wondering why this isn't a thing in the United States. Thankfully, MoDo opened up in Honolulu inside Mitsuwa market--maybe the deliciousness can make that final leap across the Pacific?
My kids love it
Awesome service, absolutely delicious and great Kamaaina deals too!
Chocolate is my favorite
Cookies n cream and Hawaiian honey
Their donuts are good . I like Lilikoi And cookies & cream donuts are so sweet and delicious! Yum! 😋
(Translated by Google) A classic Mcdo  (Original) Un Mcdo classique
Very unique donuts they are great try the chocolate!

The donuts definitely look quite different and have a unique texture too. We got a mixed half dozen and between the four of us we managed to polish the lot off in about 5 minutes! Would definitely come back and get these again anytime. All of the flavors we had were delicious!
Excellent donuts with many unique flavors to try from.  Priced at around $2 per donut with a small kama’aina discount.

Loved the idea of these unique donuts but with more abstract flavours than your traditional maple glaze at Timmie's (let's just say). I loved how the coffee had a bit of crunch to it. Would come back.
Great coffee and donuts friendly service. Alot of staff so really short wait.
Amazing little donut shop! Good breakfast waffles and located inside the Mitsuwa Marketplace
Mostly just fluffy-textured donuts, but still really delicious. I preferred the unfrosted simpler flavors.

Fun little mochi doughnut shop located in Mitsuwa marketplace (all the way in the back left corner). They offer a variety of flavors, our favorite was the cookies and cream. The top of the doughnut is more of a icing/frosting consistency, and it is this layer that gives flavor to the doughnut. We tried every flavor available that day and cookies and cream was a top favorite. The icing/frosting is very light in flavor. I would recommend this place for a doughnut or two. I fell in love with mochi doughnuts from Liliha bakery, and I have to say those are still my all time favorite, but Modo doughnuts are a close second... and they give local discount with an ID!!!
The store inside the mitsuwa. We have tried lilikoi, matcha, black sesame and houji flavour. All of them are tasty. They are soft and not too sweet. Will definitely return to try other flavours.
Modo waffle donuts were great. Mild flavor, nice consistency, and interesting high quality toppings. Nice area to sit outside the shop.
I bought in SJ mitsuwa market. Waited almost 2 hours.. But It was so good, not too sweet and soft. I only got Chocolate/green tea/ cookie and cream flavors!

Yummmmmmmmyyyyy, a bit pricey but the flavors and texture make it worth it!! The sesame seed one is delicious and I also love the Strawberry donut. They’re tucked away on the top level of the International Market Place(from the Kuhio entrance) but a must have if you’re in the Waikiki area!!

Great donut shop located inside the Mitsuwa store in International Marketplace. The donuts are nice and chewy and not too sweet. Being in the shape of a ring of little balls makes it easy to tear off pieces and share different flavours with friends. The black sesame is definitely one of their best flavours.
I almost can’t find the place . This shop is inside Mitsuwa.

I had trouble finding this hidden gem near closing time which made me too late to get the flavor I wanted but I came back the next day and they had plenty. So, it’s in the Mitsuwa Marketplace inside the International Marketplace in Waikiki. I loved these unique and tasty donuts! Best were the key lime and cookies and creme. The matcha was just okay, not enough matcha flavor and tasted bland. Other than that, they’re not overly sweet and so delicious, soft, and chewy. Will definitely be back on my next vacation!

Delicious little treat that's not too sweet. A chewy donut with a thin layer of icing. Yum! Black sesame was nutty and matcha had a nice flavour. Inside a food court in the mall on the second floor so not fancy.
Interesting place.

Addictive!  Modo inside Mitsuwa store in International Marketplace.  Saw this place was near our hotel so we went to try them. They have a lovely chewy texture and are shaped like many balls connected so they are easy to eat and share. Oreo cookie is definitely my families favourite. I enjoyed the lilikoi one as well. I agree with others that the matcha was a disappointment wish it had more flavour. Black sesame was also good. But all doughnuts were addictive and yummy.  We brought a dozen home to Canada.

It's great, I love it. It's not an ordinary "donut".  It's quite unique and refreshing. I purchased the Keylime and their number one seller the cookies and creme.  Personally I enjoyed the keylime a little better.  The texture of it is chewy, it kind of reminds me of a carnival funnel cake.  I visited on the 12th of Jan. 2018 and honestly, I've been craving it ever since.
The black sesame was awesome, but all the others were tasty too!
Very good mochi donuts and love the lilikoi and strawberry ♡ love all the flavors ♡

Woke up early and was there right when they opened, unfortunately.  Definitely one of the more trendy places on the island or as most Yelpers would deem a "gem."  Nothing too impressive about the flavors.  The matcha was definitely lacking and could've used more matcha and less sugar.  I believe whatever they use in the icing had a mild nutty flavor which over powered the black sesame donut as the flavors settled on my palette.  Also, got the coffee or espresso whatever and a key lime donut.  Overall, wasn't too impressed with the flavors. Presentation, however, is awesome.  Love the colors and interesting shape.

The tiny MoDo shop is located in the small food court area towards the back of Mitsuwa Market in the International Marketplace in Waikiki.  They sell illy coffee (hot or iced) and offer a fairly good variety of common flavors from strawberry or chocolate to unusual flavors like black sesame or lilikoi.  Each doughnut has a light texture and is nicely frosted with neither too thick or too thin sugar coating.  The display counter is visually appealing and when we ordered, the cashier selected doughnuts from a rack just behind a wall. Enjoy right there or can be packaged for take away.
Best mochi donuts

Fantastic new way to enjoy donuts! These donuts have a slight chew to them, and are dipped in amazing flavors! The flavors change occasionally, but at this time, lilikoi and black sesame are my favorites.  During my most recent visit, they had eleven flavors. Lilikoi, green tea, black sesame, espresso, Hawaiian honey, chocolate, strawberry, lime, white chocolate, cookies and cream, and Earl Grey. Prices range between flavors from $1.50 to $2.  I've so far stopped by five-ish times, each time experiencing excellent service. Especially since they just recently opened, the quality of the donuts and capability of the staff are superb.  Mention that you're kama'aina and you'll get 5% off your order. I'm not sure if MoDo stands for More Donuts or Mochi Donuts, but either way, works for me!

Damn I just died and gone to heaven after having one of these donuts.  At first I thought they were just regular donuts but I was mistaken.  They are actually mochi donuts so when eat these bad boys, it's soft and chewy at the same time.  I just can't believe how awesome this donut it.  I'm in big trouble.
